/*
:name: shift_combo_i8
:type: equiv
:verilog_top: top
:pyrope_top: shift_combo_i8.top
*/

// PASSING regression for 2i-issues E (now FIXED): a signed-shift idiom
// `(a << b) ^ (a >> b)` on i8. In an 8-bit assignment context the left shift
// wraps to the low 8 bits and the right shift is arithmetic (sign-preserving).
//
// cgen used to emit the SRA term bare (`a >>> amt`) next to the unsigned SHL
// zero-extend idiom `({N{1'b0}} | a) << amt`; Verilog then evaluated the XOR in
// unsigned context, demoting the `>>>` to a logical shift -> wrong for negative
// a (was 384/1024 mismatches). cgen now emits the term self-contained as
// `$signed($signed(a) >>> amt)`. Verified 0/1024 mismatches under iverilog and
// PROVEN equivalent under both cvc5 (on the LGraph) and lgyosys (on the cgen
// output).
pub comb top(a:s8, b:u2) -> (r:s8) {
  wrap r = (a << b) ^ (a >> b)
}
